<li id="_note-207"><b><a href="#_ref-207">^</a></b> Scott Mendelson．-{“}-<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/scott-mendelson/huff-post-review---star-t_b_200098.html" class="external text" rel="nofollow">-{zh;zh-hans;zh-hant|HuffPost Review -- Star Trek (2009)}-</a>-{”}-，<span class="ILHItem"><span class="ILHChinese"><a href="/w/index.php?title=%E8%B5%AB%E8%8A%AC%E9%A1%BF%E9%82%AE%E6%8A%A5&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="赫芬顿邮报（尚未撰写）">赫芬顿邮报</a></span><span class="ILHComment" style="display:none;">（<span style="font-size:smaller;"><span class="ILHLang">英语</span>：</span><span class="ILHOriginal" lang="en" style="font-size:smaller;" xml:lang="en">-{<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Huffington_Post" class="extiw" title="en:The Huffington Post">The Huffington Post</a>}-</span>）</span></span>，2009年5月8日．於2009年6月4日查阅．原文：“this film is Star Trek for people who have never seen the shows or the movies, and furthermore need their characters drawn in broad strokes and the philosophies explicitly explained in monologue.”<span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adc&amp;rft.type=newspaperArticle&amp;rft.subject=News&amp;rft.au=Scott+Mendelson&amp;rft.title=HuffPost+Review+--+Star+Trek+%282009%29&amp;rft.identifier=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Fscott-mendelson%2Fhuff-post-review---star-t_b_200098.html&amp;rft.publisher=%3Cspan+class%3D%22ILHItem%22%3E%3Cspan+class%3D%22ILHChinese%22%3E%5B%5B%E8%B5%AB%E8%8A%AC%E9%A1%BF%E9%82%AE%E6%8A%A5%7C%E8%B5%AB%E8%8A%AC%E9%A1%BF%E9%82%AE%E6%8A%A5%5D%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan+class%3D%22ILHComment%22+style%3D%22display%3Anone%3B%22%3E%EF%BC%88%3Cspan+style%3D%22font-size%3Asmaller%3B%22%3E%3Cspan+class%3D%22ILHLang%22%3E%E8%8B%B1%E8%AF%AD%3C%2Fspan%3E%EF%BC%9A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan+class%3D%22ILHOriginal%22+lang%3D%22en%22+style%3D%22font-size%3Asmaller%3B%22%3E-%7B%5B%5B%3Aen%3AThe+Huffington+Post%7CThe+Huffington+Post%5D%5D%7D-%3C%2Fspan%3E%EF%BC%89%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%